def: One who bears arms, but has no title.
A sea robin having large, winglike pectoral fins. See Searobin, under Robin.
The spar upon which the upper edge of a fore-and-aft sail isextended.
One who has an advowson. Cowell.
A salt of saccholactactic acid; -- formerly called alsosaccholate. [Obs.] See Mucate.

Of or pertaining to heat; due to heat; thermal; as, thermiclines. Thermic balance. See Bolometer.-- Thermic fever (Med.), the condition of fever produced bysunstroke. See Sunstroke.-- Thermic weight. (Mech.) Same as Heat weight, under Heat.
Deviation from correct orthography; bad spelling. [Obs.]Feltham.
